texts.text: >Your vision blurs and it becomes hard to stay standing.
*Wince*
Ugh! What's going on?!
You're all there, right? I can't see anything!
Are you guys close by?!
I can hear you, so you must be close...
But that thing has us dead to rites...!
Just believe, y'all!
Believe?! Believe what?!
Believe in your bond.
Believe in Fellowship.
Yo, Newbie's got the right idea. We gotta believe in our bond.
Yo, Newbie's got the right idea. We gotta believe in our Fellowship.
Vince even said so, right?
Believe in each other...
Yeah, okay. I'll try to remember that feeling from before...!
>Everyone closes their eyes and looks into their hearts.
>Then, you all open your eyes at once...
My eyes, I can see better...
I can see you guys now...!
Yes! I feel our bond very strongly!
Wait, it's coming!
Get ready!
We got this.
Let's go.
Together!
Right!
>Your demon jumps out in front at the same time as Rika's,
>and they perform a vicious pincer move!
*Groan*
It worked!
Yeah! Keep it up!
>The Liberators unleash successive combo attacks.
Let's go!
>Jeng Yun aims for Nyarlathotep's head.
I can read you like a... What?!
Jeng Yun was just a decoy. We were going after your wings.
Flying seemed a little unfair, so we're evening the odds.
Surprise!
Let's go!
>Shiori and Seiran attack from both sides and break its wings.
Next... Yo, it feels too good to gang up on this thing.
Ain't that the truth. Let me at him too!
Eat this!
>Vince's attack pierces Nyarlathotep's chest!

*Snicker*
Heh...
Huh? Is it not working?
Fear not. That last one was more than effective.
If you say so. How does one more sound? A parting gift from all of us?!
>The Liberators attack Nyarlathotep all at once.
To think that you'd be able to see through all this chaos.
See? Having "friends" isn't so bad, right?

*Laugh*
That may be.
But...
You speak for your friends, but how about all these other people?
Some fell to the chaos and even killed their own loved ones...
You too have blood on your hands, no?
What the hell's your point?!
Humans are fickle creatures.
I simply made it clear to you, the masters of this world, just how true this is.
After just a small taste of my chaos,
you nearly ended yourselves.
I delighted in seeing everything unfold.
But you entertained me through different means.
You already caused so much pain and now you're spouting this nonsense.

*Snicker*
I am sufficiently satisfied.
It's starting to fade...?!
Humans...
When this world is once again mired in chaos, when lies and truth meld together,
will your precious beliefs help you overcome it...?
>As Nyarlathotep's voice begins to fade, the world slowly returns to normal.
>Nyarlathotep finally disappears completely...
>A few days later...
Honey's back!
Hey.
Honey! You're all okay now?!
Yes, Honey's back to 100%!
It'll take more than just stopping me from breathing to kill me!
Thank god...
But Vince has been doing maintenance on me nonstop.
He might be more tired than I am.
Nah, there's no way.
But what about Nyarlathotep? How have things been after all that?
The world is close to being free from the taint of chaos.
On the news,
it's being called a sort of hysteria the world has never seen.
It sounds like people don't know about any demons being involved.
But there were so many casualties. So many deaths.
Yo, we believe in "Fellowship".
But that thing...
It showed that it just hangs by a tiny thread.
It made me sick to be honest.
And the last thing it said before it disappeared...
"When this world is once again mired in chaos..."
Does it plan on coming back?
I don't know, but...
If it comes back when we're not prepared to believe in each other like we were today...
If everybody everywhere stops believing in each other,
we won't be able to believe in each other or even ourselves...
I'm not sure I do even now.
I'm scared that I'll end up pointing my gun at one of you...
Nobody believed anything Honey said during all that too...
Honey isn't a human or a demon.
But Honey has a soul just like anyone else.
Honey believes that we're connected and bound together.
But Honey also learned that our bond can be broken easily.
I learned this too...
Believing in our bond...
It helped us find something deeper and more real than that.
Yo, she's right. Where we're from and how we look don't matter.
We're all connected by our bond.
The Liberators are about believing in one another. I believe we will be okay.
Yes, there's only one thing we need to believe in.
The "Fellowship" we worked so hard to find and establish.
You're saying that simply being connected won't be enough.
Yes, a deep "Fellowship"...
Yo, if any of us start doin' somethin' fishy again, just sock it to us good.
You know, like Vince did.
Honey. I don't know what to say...
I was convinced that you were a demon.
Even when you knew the entire time who I was.
It's okay.
I feel like our "Fellowship" became stronger.
While Honey was out for the count,
I felt our "Fellowship" through everyone's souls.
It even looked like a bright, glowing cable that tied us together!
When Honey saw that it went through Honey's soul too,
Honey couldn't help but cry.
People cry when they feel sorrow, joy and pain.
Honey? You cried...?
Hehe. Honey's a special Homunculus after all!
